5|$|Many writers {{wrote about}} the deeds of Odaenathus; Nicostratus of Trebizond {{probably}} accompanied the king on his campaigns and wrote a history of that period starting from Philip the Arab and ending shortly before the king's death. According to Potter, Nicostratus' account was meant to glorify Odaenathus and <b>demonstrate</b> <b>his</b> superiority over Roman emperors.|$|E
